Name: Me
Message: Hey Inessa, it's Andrew Konoff. How many Tupperware of cocktail shrimp did you manage to snag?
Enough to last me through the night- so obviously not enough.

Name: Me
Message: It's hard to have enough when you're dealing in finite numbers.
They really ought to have just infinite shrimp at these things- it was the aquarium after all.

Name: Me
Message: Right? I'd talk to the Olive Garden folks and see what sorcery gets them all those breadsticks
Definitely some sort of dark magic from what I gather.

Name: Me
Message: They're obviously pretty metal. Not as metal as me though, falling asleep at 11
Oh I know how that goes. 11 pm bedtime is all the rage these days.

Name: Me
Message: Burning that late evening oil. You more on the early bird or night owl side of things?
Night owl given the freedom. But the work schedule has forced me to be an early bird. The things we do for money. How about yourself?

Name: Me
Message: Owl for sure. I get to set my own schedule, which means I slowly devolve into going to sleep at 3am

Name: Me
Message: Or not sleeping at all. Who needs it! Not future humans
That sounds very much like my schedule given the chance- I always do my best work between 12 and 3. The future needs to hurry up and get with the program
, there's too much to get done.

Name: Me
Message: I am the exact same way. In exactly fifteen minutes I will need to make something.
Well best of luck with whatever you'll be working on. Unfortunately I ought to turn in for the night if I want to avoid being a zombie at work tomorrow.
Pleasure to meet you today.

Name: Me
Message: A pleasure on my end too. Sleep well.

Name: Me
Message: Howdy Inessa. How'd your weekend go? Full of sunny adventures?
Hey Andrew. My weekend wasn't very adventurous but it was very relaxing so I have no complaints. How about yours?

Name: Me
Message: Pretty good overall - spent a ton of time in trinbell. I'm moving to that hood in July and am trying to get used to the whole 'drinking and picnicking in the park' thing. It's a tough life.
I can attest to that- that's exactly what I was doing. Spent most of my Sunday there.

Name: Me
Message: Nice. I have a feeling like the whole city ends up there at some point in a weekend. You live in the west end?
Yeah it definitely seems that way. I do indeed- very close to the park. You?

Name: Me
Message: I'm currently up in roncesvalles - land of strollers and brunch. Moving to queen and Palmerston for July, and I can't wait.
But close to delicious Polish sausages at least? That's fun though- this area it's definitely a bit more lively.

Name: Me
Message: I will be missing the sausage for sure. No innuendo there. I will actually be a bit sad. And the perogies! Oh man.

Name: Me
Message: Actually, I've had a craving for perogies lately. We should go to czehoski on queen and indulge. Are you free Saturday night?
Ahhh can never go wrong with perogies, I've never had them at Czehoski's. I do believe I'm free that night- what time works for you?

Name: Me
Message: I was thinking 8:00. That work for you?
Sure, 8 is fine.

Name: Me
Message: Awesome. Fair warning, I like sauerkraut.
Who doesn't?

Name: Me
Message: You are saying all the right things, you know.
It's easy to say the right things when it comes to food.

Name: Me
Message: Yeah, but only if your mouth isn't full. Then it's a lot harder.

Name: Me
Message: Anyway, I'm excited to learn a bit more about you on Saturday. I gotta get back to coding for now - see you in a few days!
Good point. Likewise! Good luck with coding, see you Saturday.

Name: Me
Message: Hey lady, just checking that we're on for 8.
Hey! Yeah I'm still down.

Name: Me
Message: Wonderful. Hope you're enjoying your Saturday - see ya in a few.
Likewise! See you soon.

Name: Me
Message: Got a spot on the patio upstairs. I'm the one wearing a leather vest

Name: Me
Message: (Jokes)
Be there in 2!

Name: Me
Message: Ohh no, I really hope I didn't give you my cold.
I'll know who to blame if that's the case.

Name: Me
Message: I will be very sorry if so. Currently I am not sorry ðŸ˜—

Name: Me
Message: Hey lady. How did the application go? Not too painful to revisit past work, I hope.

Name: Me
Message: Hey - tried texting you last week. You get done everything you wanted to?
Hey, sorry it's been a hectic week. Sort of, still have quite a bit to do for the submission next week. Hope everything went well with yours!

Name: Me
Message: It went pretty good - except the persistent cold, which has been devastating to my Kleenex reserves.

Name: Me
Message: That's a shame you're so busy. This weekend I am too, but I think we should grab coffee and explore high park together for part of one afternoon. How about Sunday?

Hey, glad everything went well! Sorry to hear about your cold though. So I'm not very good at this but I just gotta tell ya- you seem really cool, but as much as I enjoyed our meeting I'm afraid I'm not feeling much more than just friendliness. I hope you understand. Best of luck with your app and all the best.

Name: Me
Message: Wow, normally I'm actually good at reading when that's the case, but definitely thought you were game. Thanks for being honest, Inessa.
